# Company Intelligence Extractor

## Overview

Company Intelligence Extractor is an end-to-end NLP and Machine Learning pipeline that analyses company websites and predicts their business sector.

The project automatically:

* Scrapes company homepages
* Extracts and cleans website text
* Identifies keywords using KeyBERT
* Extracts named entities using spaCy
* Classifies companies into sectors using TF-IDF and Logistic Regression
* Evaluates model performance using Cross Validation and Holdout Testing

---

## Project Workflow

Company Website URL

↓

HTML Scraping

↓

Content Cleaning

↓

Keyword Extraction (KeyBERT)

↓

Named Entity Recognition (spaCy)

↓

TF-IDF Feature Engineering

↓

Logistic Regression Classification

↓

Sector Prediction

---

## Features

### Web Scraping

* Downloads company homepage content
* Uses file-based caching to reduce repeated requests
* Handles network errors gracefully
* Implements polite scraping with configurable delays

### Text Processing

* Removes HTML noise such as:

  * Navigation menus
  * Headers and footers
  * Cookie banners
  * GDPR popups
* Normalises extracted text
* Filters low-quality pages

### Keyword Extraction

Primary method:

* KeyBERT

Fallback method:

* TF-IDF keyword extraction

### Named Entity Recognition

Extracts:

* Organisations (ORG)
* Products (PRODUCT)
* Countries and cities (GPE)
* Locations (LOC)

### Sector Classification

Model Pipeline:

* TF-IDF Vectorizer
* Logistic Regression

Techniques used:

* N-grams (1–2)
* Vocabulary control
* L2 regularisation
* Class balancing

---

## Evaluation

The project evaluates performance using:

### Stratified Cross Validation

Provides:

* Mean Accuracy
* Standard Deviation
* Fold Scores

### Holdout Test Set

Provides:

* Precision
* Recall
* F1-score
* Classification Report

### Confusion Matrix

Used for error analysis and model diagnostics.

